title: >-
  Mastering the Multi-Resume Strategy: Tailoring Your Technical Identity with
  GetHired AI
---
In the modern high-growth tech market, the "one-size-fits-all" resume is a relic of the past. If you are a versatile engineer, you likely wear many hats—perhaps you're a React specialist by day but a Python automation enthusiast by night.

At **GetHired**, we’ve engineered our platform to support up to five distinct resumes in your library. Here is why this is the ultimate "cheat code" for your job search and how our **Ask AI** feature turns these documents into your most powerful advocates.

## The Myth of the Generalist Resume

When a recruiter at a startup looks for a "Backend Engineer," they aren't just looking for someone who *can* do the job; they are looking for someone who *is* a backend expert. If your resume spends 50% of its space talking about your CSS skills, you’re losing valuable "signal" for that specific role.

**The Multi-Resume Advantage:**

- **Role Segmentation:** Create one resume focused on your Frontend expertise (Next.js, Tailwind, Performance) and another for Fullstack or Lead roles.
- **Industry Alignment:** Tailor your project descriptions for Fintech (emphasizing security/concurrency) vs. E-commerce (emphasizing scale/analytics).
- **Seniority Tweak:** Have one version that highlights your "Individual Contributor" technical depth and another that showcases your "Team Lead" or "Mentorship" achievements.

## Ask AI: Choosing Your Voice

One of our most powerful features, **Ask AI**, acts as your 24/7 career coach. Whether you're asking the AI to draft a cover letter or explain a complex job requirement, context is everything.

Inside the **Ask AI** interface, you aren't stuck with a single data source. You get a **Resume Context Selector** that lets you choose exactly which "Professional Identity" the AI should use for the conversation.

### How it Works:

1. **Select Context:** Before starting a prompt, you can toggle between your "Senior Fullstack" resume or your "AI/ML" resume.
1. **Contextual Synthesis:** The AI reads the specific bullet points, tech stacks, and metrics from *that specific document*.
1. **Tailored Output:** If you ask, *"Write a cover letter for this Stripe role,"* and you've selected your Fintech-heavy resume, the AI will automatically weave in your most relevant financial data processing metrics.

## The Primary Resume & The AI Feed

While you can have many resumes, you designate one as your **Primary**. This is the document our internal AI uses to rank your job feed and create your personalized job digest.

When you change your primary resume, our backend instantly recalculates your **Match Scores** across thousands of active listings. This means you can "pivot" your job search in seconds—switching from looking for Frontend roles to Backend roles just by swapping your primary document and watching your feed re-align.

## Start Building Your Library

Stop compromising your experience to fit onto one page. Use **GetHired** to build a modular professional identity. Upload your variations, use them as context in **Ask AI**, and let our semantic engine find the roles that match the *specific* version of you that you want to promote today.

